Rajasthan
Nov 17, 2014
Abuse
Description:
			Two persons were arrested by the police for allegedly threatening a woman and calling her a witch in Rajasamand district, police said today.

The accused identified as Nawla (75) and his son Nathu (50), were arrested yesterday following a complaint by the 40-year-old woman alleging that they threatened her and called her a witch, SHO Delwara police station Gajendra Singh said.

They were later released, he said, adding, the matter was under investigation.

